{"TopicId":182101,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Science \u0026#039;Masks\u0026#039;","CreatedByName":"Qwarkk","CreatedById":154770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T18:54:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Qwarkk","CreatedById":154770,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T18:54:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the most frustrating things in KSP is designing a vessel with lots of scientific experiments included, successfully launching it, reaching your destination and finding that half the scientific experiments you brought along cant be run. So i was wondering if a mod exists that adds to the description of the science experiments (ie via a general patch) to show where the experiment can be run.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI understand this is controlled by the situationMask and biomeMask values in a scientific experiement\u0027s .cfg file, so if no such mod exists I will have a crack at it myself, although im not sure about the distribution rules surrounding a mod that edits Squad\u00A0 / other mod parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T20:21:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot exactly what you\u2019re asking for, but this mod tells you when you can perform scientific experiments:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4281367170\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/107661-ksp-145-x-science-ksp-science-report-and-checklist-v517/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:247px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T23:00:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182101\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549911287\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Qwarkk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Qwarkk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndistribution\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E rules surrounding a mod that edits Squad\u00A0 / other mo\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ed parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is exactly what module manager does, and it hasn\u0027t been taken down yet! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Espatie","CreatedById":194327,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T00:40:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLoads of mods edit Stock parts, be it by changing the artwork or by adding new capabilities or deleting other bits. Just make sure your mod is doing it by editing the properties of the other item in the loading process,\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E actually editing the cfg file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:47:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154770-qwarkk/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154770\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154770-qwarkk/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Qwarkk\u003C/a\u003E The exact mod for you does exist. Look here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1463971106\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179661-15-extended-information-about-scientific-experiments-in-vab-sph/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}